http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Mangalore/Caution-against-misuse-of-concessions/article14020246.ece

The Southern Railways has said that passengers found travelling on ‘senior citizen concession’ by giving false declaration on age, will be charged with the difference between the concessional fare paid and the non-concessional fare payable, plus penalty from February 1.If they are found travelling on ‘senior citizen concession’ with their berths booked under ‘senior citizen quota’, by providing false declaration of age, they will be treated as travelling without ticket, and will be penalised accordingly.